                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1200">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115R39/54</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guaymas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-06T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yaqui Indians attacked Esperanza to-day burning headquarters Richardson
                    Construction Company. Indians are still in valley. General Mange leaving from
                    here with four hundred soldiers this afternoon. Endeavor restore order. About
                    thirty Americans known to be in valley. No details of fighting. Nothing known
                    yet of welfare House in battle. Letter from auditor Richardson Company says
                    nothing beyond reporting attack and burning of headquarters.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
